definition.value: A glycopentaosylceramide having N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucose as the pentasaccharide component.
A myo-inositol pentakisphosphate comprising 1D-myo-inositol having the five phosphate groups placed in the 1-' 2-' 4-, 5- and 6-positions.
The cis,cis-isomer of  muconic acid. It is produced during the degradation of chlorobenzene by bacteria like Bacillus.
